# Forms

Compose forms use SvelteKit's form actions + `use:enhance`. The actions are
defined in `+page.server.ts` by Claude; you wire the UI.

## Reading the server contract

Before writing a form, read the matching `+page.server.ts` to learn:

1. What actions are defined (e.g., `?/update`, `?/archive`)
2. What form fields each action validates (via the Zod schema in `src/lib/validation.ts`)
3. What the return shape is (`{ note }`, `{ success: true }`, `fail(400, {...})`)

If you're missing any of this, stop — ask for a handoff note from Claude.

## Form template

```svelte
<!-- src/routes/(app)/notes/[id]/+page.svelte -->
<script lang="ts">
  import { enhance } from '$app/forms';
  import { Button } from '$lib/components/ui/button';
  import { Input } from '$lib/components/ui/input';

  let { data, form } = $props();

  // Track submitting state for optimistic UI.
  let submitting = $state(false);
</script>

<form
  method="POST"
  action="?/update"
  use:enhance={() => {
    submitting = true;
    return async ({ update }) => {
      await update({ reset: false });  // keep user's input on error
      submitting = false;
    };
  }}
>
  <Input name="title" value={form?.title ?? data.note.title} required />
  <Input name="body" value={form?.body ?? data.note.body} />

  {#if form?.errors?.title}
    <p role="alert" class="text-destructive text-sm">{form.errors.title}</p>
  {/if}

  <Button type="submit" disabled={submitting}>
    {submitting ? 'Saving…' : 'Save'}
  </Button>
</form>

<form method="POST" action="?/archive" use:enhance>
  <Button type="submit" variant="destructive">Archive</Button>
</form>
```

## The `form` prop

`form` is populated with the server action's return value (or the `fail()`
payload). Use it to:
- Re-render with user input after validation failures
- Surface error messages from the server
- Show success confirmations

## Progressive enhancement

`use:enhance` is the pattern. Without JS, forms still post and reload the
page (SvelteKit handles the round trip). With JS, the response updates
`form` in place without a full reload.

Never write `onclick` handlers that manually `fetch()` — that bypasses the
form-action contract and won't work without JS.

## Imperative submission

For buttons not inside a `<form>` (rare), use `applyAction`:

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import { applyAction, deserialize } from '$app/forms';

  async function share(noteId: string): Promise<void> {
    const body = new FormData();
    body.set('noteId', noteId);
    const res = await fetch('?/share', { method: 'POST', body });
    const result = deserialize(await res.text());
    await applyAction(result);
  }
</script>
```

## Don't

- Don't invent form field names that don't exist in the Zod schema — check `src/lib/validation.ts`
- Don't show loading spinners for forms; use the submit button's disabled state
- Don't swallow the `form` prop's error state — always surface it
- Don't use `on:submit|preventDefault` and hand-roll fetch — use `use:enhance`
